<p>
The following horoscopes are written for Rising signs but relevant for Sun & Moon signs based on derived houses.
</p>

<h2>Aries</h2>
<p>
This week you may find yourself forming a more intense connection with someone you previously saw in a casual way. This could be a friendship evolving into a collaborative partnership or a budding romance. At the same time, doubts around the sincerity of the connection creep in. The underlying theme is your relationship to receiving, especially if you feel you have to work harder than others to prove your value. This week asks you to soften that pattern and return to a more compassionate view of yourself.
Friday’s Full Moon in Scorpio illuminates where you have been over-investing in a shared dynamic emotionally, financially, or energetically. What changes is that you can now pinpoint exactly what you haven’t been able to express out loud before. This marks a turning point in how you approach intimacy, trust, and reciprocity. Honest communication about your needs may close out an old relational pattern where you’ve accepted vagueness and open the door to something more tangibly rewarding.
</p>

<h2>Taurus</h2>
<p>
This week you may feel a strong pull toward a career path or public role that has real implications for your finances and close relationships. Moving forward may require letting go of something familiar that you’ve leaned on for security. At the same time, questions around validation and what is worth your time, energy, or emotional investment surface.
Friday’s Full Moon in Scorpio brings this into focus through your relationships and agreements. You may start to see where a connection or professional dynamic has shifted, especially if you have been giving more than you are receiving. There can be a realization that something no longer holds the same meaning, or value, as it once did. This may not be easy to fully process in the moment, but what becomes visible now changes how you approach commitment, reciprocity, and who you choose to build a future with.
</p>

<h2>Gemini</h2>
<p>
This week you may feel increasingly frustrated with your daily routine or a work or health issue that does not seem to be improving. It seems your normal remedy is no longer effective, which pushes you to consider a more unusual approach. An alternative method that catches your attention could feel like a shot in the dark, but it’s worth exploring.
Friday’s Full Moon in Scorpio offers a deeper or more intensive way of addressing your issue. As you look further into it, you may come across people who have experienced something similar. Seeing your experience reflected back to you helps you understand it more clearly. What begins as a workaround may shift your overall approach to personal wellness.
</p>

<h2>Cancer</h2>
<p>
This week, self-reflection alerts you to patterns within your emotional foundations. This may come through an unexpected conversation, therapy session, or learning experience that helps you see something more clearly. As this shifts, a shared responsibility or emotional weight you have been carrying begins to lighten, feeling easier to talk about.
Under Friday’s Full Moon in Scorpio, it’s time to play, create, or reconnect with something that brings delight. This can be through romance, time with children, or simply being present in the moment—no overthinking what’s going on in the background. Lighten the mood by prioritizing what feels good without guilt.
</p>

<h2>Leo</h2>
<p>
This is a favorable week to negotiate a raise or advocate for yourself at work. You’re persuasive, clear, and secure in what you bring to the table. This applies to any audience, so if you have something passionate to say on social media, put it out there. Asserting yourself now not only feels empowering, it sets the tone for taking bigger risks in the future.
Under Friday’s Full Moon in Scorpio, you’re ready to turn inward. Quiet reflection may bring up deep emotions, and memories feel especially meaningful when shared with family. This is a powerful time to honor loved ones. Water feels grounding now, so consider swimming or simply slowing down near it. Be mindful of overindulgence; set limits where needed.
</p>

<h2>Virgo</h2>
<p>
This week, you could receive praise for your work or skills in leveraging resources to solve a problem or gain an edge. If you need support you’ll have the right people’s ear. Once you have the spotlight, the urge to present a perfectly curated version of yourself may be strong, but what your audience would best respond to is your humility. Being honest about your shortcomings makes you more relatable and strengthens your credibility.
Under Friday’s Full Moon, you may find yourself searching for answers about a friendship or a plan that feels out of reach. You may feel sentimental and melancholic, wondering where it all went wrong. If you can’t find closure, focus on what the experience taught you and how it prepared you for what comes next.
</p>

<h2>Libra</h2>
<p>
This week, you may realize a risk you took was well worth it. A decision you second-guessed, especially around spending or travel, proves to be a meaningful investment in your well-being. It’s a reminder of how easily overthinking and guilt can deny you the self-care that allows you to show up with compassion in your daily life. This brings you back to your “why.”
Under Friday’s Full Moon in Scorpio, an honest conversation in a close relationship, possibly with someone younger, may hit a sensitive spot. Still, this moment opens space to confront perfectionist tendencies that quietly erode your confidence. Don’t let that critical voice overshadow the kindness, sensitivity, and care that make a deeper impact than you give yourself credit for.
</p>

<h2>Scorpio</h2>
<p>
This week, you’re no longer in the dark about a situation that once troubled you. With this clarity comes a deeper sense of security and trust in where you stand. If you’re struggling to find the right words with a child or romantic partner, remember that your presence speaks louder than words. The emotional bond you share is deeply felt regardless of acknowledgment.
Under Friday’s Full Moon in Scorpio, your own needs require attention after a period of tending to everyone else. You may hesitate to ask for recognition, but sustained avoidance allows resentment to build. This is your moment to be honest and assert yourself. Taking space to decompress is not selfish—it’s necessary.
</p>

<h2>Sagittarius</h2>
<p>
This week, a conversation with a friend or co-worker may lead to an invitation to collaborate. This person has noticed your creativity, and they admire the way you think. Engaging with this may take you outside your comfort zone, but it could also feel surprisingly aligned if you choose to explore it.
Under Friday’s Full Moon in Scorpio, you’re reflecting on information you haven’t really shared with anyone. Your intuition may have foreshadowed an event that is now unfolding. There’s a sense of relief and validation in trusting yourself. You may feel tempted to say “I told you so,” but you’re being called to exercise discretion and compassion instead. Sometimes it matters more to be kind than to be right.
</p>

<h2>Capricorn</h2>
<p>
This week, an opportunity to learn through creativity and experimentation could boost both your confidence and earning potential. You might feel pressure to perform well, but you’ll have support and encouragement from your peers.
Under Friday’s Full Moon in Scorpio, someone in your circle could surprise you. This may be a family member or acquaintance you felt frustrated with in the past, but now there’s an opportunity to enjoy each other’s company. They may turn out to be more fun than you expected and offer insights that support your goals.
</p>

<h2>Aquarius</h2>
<p>
This week, taking creative risks pays off. You may not have felt this authentically yourself in a long time. As you become more self-sufficient, your work becomes more reflective of your personal values.
Under Friday’s Full Moon in Scorpio, there may be a spotlight on a project you’ve been working on. You might shy away from the attention, especially if it means explaining yourself to people who don’t immediately understand. Still, this is an opportunity to be recognized in a way you’ll need to grow comfortable with as your distinct voice draws more attention.
</p>

<h2>Pisces</h2>
<p>
This week, you may realize there won’t be closure on an ending you can’t fully explain. Spending time alone in reflection allows you to focus on personal growth as you regain a sense of security.
Under Friday’s Full Moon in Scorpio, you’re balancing your need for comfort with a desire to explore something deeper. A sense of nostalgia may draw you back to a place, idea, or memory from the past. Revisiting it could offer both clarity and a moment of escape.
</p>

